# Apache / SiteGround / cPanel hosting — point any 404 at our themed page.
#
# If you deploy this folder as the document root of a subdomain (e.g.
# docs.example.com → docs/), the ErrorDocument path below works as-is.
#
# If you deploy under a sub-path (e.g. example.com/docs/), change the
# directive to:
#     ErrorDocument 404 /docs/404.html
#
# Netlify uses docs/404.html automatically and ignores this file. The file
# is harmless on hosts that don't support .htaccess.

ErrorDocument 404 /404.html
